I hate this Little Caesars. The service is slow, the manager is discourteous and impolite.  While visiting I arrived to see several people waiting impatiently, I was there too pick-up an online order.  I retrieved my order rather quickly since it was not a walk in.  Except that part of my order was missing??? UGH....When I ask the cashier a young woman, she asks the manager...who has no answer and no consideration for my investment of time.   I gave myself the ,"I told you so speech", as I had experienced a similar incident about two months ago.  (In the prior incident), they didn't make the pizza according to what I ordered...got it home had to bring it all the way back... I was not happy but definitely not rude.  Some words exchange and the  SAME  manager as tonight, makes a snide rude comment....TO WHICH I ANSWERED.  Anyway no need to rehash, this Little Caesars needs to demote this manager, and hire someone competent. The cashier, a young woman, should be promoted to manager; she was very polite and apologetic.
